+ Initialise Server
 - Install XAMPP
 - Open Terminal
+ Run sudo /opt/lampp/lampp start
+ Edit opt/lampp/htdocs/index.php to point to desired Folder 
  hence on typing localhost in browser will point to desired folder[/WebFolder]
+ Open Desired Web Browser: Firefox/Chrome...
+ Type in Address Bar: localhost(=http://localhost)[Check OK]

+ Initialise Sensor
 - Connect uP with EthernetShield, LDR
 - Connect uP to LAN Port, PowerSupply
 - Start Arduino IDE
 - if (enc28j60 arduino shield used):
   - Install Ethershieldeldo Library
   - Upload bms.ino arduino server sketch to arduino board
   else if (default arduino ethernet shield being used):
   - Load Ethernet Library webserver example, 
   - Edit network settings and webpage serving format
   - Upload the edited webserver example sketch to the board
 - Ping Sensor IP Address(set in uploaded sketch) from WebBrowser: [Check OK]

+ Auto Sensing
 - Open Terminal
 - Navigate 2 Web Folder/sense [e.g opt/lampp/htdocs/xampp/example/WeBuild/sense]
 - sudo chmod -R 777 WebFolder/sense
 - Run ./sense.sh from terminal

+ Web Development
 + Edit Contents in sda5/WebBuild/
 + Delete webfolder location 
   # sudo rm -r opt/lampp/htdocs/xampp/example/WebBuild #
 + sudo cp -r /media/sda5/WebBuild opt/lampp/htdocs/xampp/example/
 + Reload Page on Web Browser [http://localhost]
 OR
 + Open Terminal
 + Navigate to Website Folder 
   # cd /opt/lampp/htdocs/spectroserver #
 + Edit required files
   # sudo gedit /file/to/edit #
 + Reload Page on Web Browser[http://localhost]
 OR
 + GitHub for Version Control, Code Distribution and Collaborative Editing
  + Clone Online Directory to Offline working directory
    # cd /path/to/offline/dir #
    # git clone http://www.ruleoneonzero@bitbucket.com/spectroserver.git #
  + Edit pages in offline directory and Stage edited files
    # git add . #
    OR 
    # git add /path/to/edited/file #
  + Sync with Website Folder [/opt/lampp/htdocs/spectroserver]
    # sudo rsync -vur --delete --exclude=*.git* --exclude=*#* --exclude=*~ /path/to/working/directory path/to/web/serving/directory/
  + Verify Code functioning by reloading page on Web Browser[http://localhost]
  + If Working, Upload to Git Repository
    # git commit -m "Commit Message" #
  + Push a set of changes to online repositories
    # git push origin master/branchname #
  + To setup online repository
    # git remote add http://debanjum@bitbucket.com/spectroserver #
    # git push -u origin --all #
    # git push -u origin --tags #
